---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 6, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Lone Meeple"
  description="Privacy policy for the Lone Meeple mobile application."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-bark">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-bark/50">Lone Meeple</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-bark/40 mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose-article">
        <p>
          This privacy policy applies to <strong>Lone Meeple</strong>, the solo
          board-gaming companion published by Fjord Labs (the “App”). We are
          committed to keeping your data private: we do not sell, rent, or
          share your personal information with advertisers or third-party
          marketers, and we collect only what the App needs to work.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Collect</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Account information.</strong> When you sign in, we store
            the account identifier provided by your chosen sign-in method
            (email address, Apple Sign In, or Google). Authentication is
            handled securely through Supabase.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your solo journal.</strong> The games you add, the plays
            you log (scores, results, difficulty, duration, dates, notes), and
            your campaign progress are stored with your account so your
            journal is backed up and follows you across devices.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> collect data for advertising, tracking,
          or profiling, and the App contains no analytics SDKs.
        </p>

        <h2>Shared Account Across Fjord Apps</h2>

        <p>
          Lone Meeple uses the shared Fjord Apps authentication system, so one
          account signs you in to any of our apps. Your account identity is
          shared across the apps, but your Lone Meeple journal is used only to
          operate Lone Meeple for you.
        </p>

        <h2>Purchases</h2>

        <p>
          Lone Meeple offers a one-time Pro unlock. Payments are processed
          entirely by Apple; we never see your payment details. We use
          RevenueCat to associate your purchase with your account so it can be
          restored on any device.
        </p>

        <h2>AI Recap (optional)</h2>

        <p>
          Pro users can generate a short written recap of their stats. When
          you use this feature, the relevant statistics — play counts, win
          rates, streaks, and the titles of your most-played games — are sent
          to Anthropic solely to generate the text of the recap. Nothing else
          from your journal is shared, and this happens only when you tap the
          recap button.
        </p>

        <h2>Board Game Catalog</h2>

        <p>
          Game names and cover images in the search catalog are provided by
          BoardGameGeek and loaded from their servers. Lone Meeple is an
          unofficial companion: it stores only your own data, and all game
          names and trademarks belong to their respective owners.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>

        <p>
          Your data is stored using Supabase, which provides secure,
          industry-standard infrastructure for authentication and database
          storage. Access controls ensure only your account can read and
          write your data.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>

        <p>
          We keep your data for as long as you maintain an account. You can
          delete your account and your entire journal at any time from within
          the App (Settings → Delete account &amp; my data). Once deleted,
          your data is removed from our systems.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

        <p>
          The App is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do
          not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we do, we
          will revise the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>

        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Email
          <a href="mailto:fjordlabs.app@gmail.com">fjordlabs.app@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
